#### 1.4 - Export CSV/JSON
**Description:** Permettre l'export de tous les rapports en CSV ou JSON.

**Boutons dans l'interface reports (admin/controller/module/debug_logger.php méthode reports()):**
```php
// Dans le HTML généré, ajouter après les filtres:
$h .= '<div class="export-btns" style="margin-left:auto">';
$h .= '<a href="' . htmlspecialchars($base . '&action=export&format=csv') . '" class="btn-export">Export CSV</a>';
$h .= '<a href="' . htmlspecialchars($base . '&action=export&format=json') . '" class="btn-export">Export JSON</a>';
$h .= '</div>';

// Traiter l'action export:
if ($action === 'export') {
    $format = $this->request->get['format'] ?? 'csv';
    $this->exportReports($format, $filter_status, $filter_source);
    return;
}
```

**Nouvelle méthode exportReports():**
```php
private function exportReports(string $format, int $filter_status, string $filter_source): void {
    $this->load->model('extension/debug_logger/module/debug_logger');
    $reports = $this->model_extension_debug_logger_module_debug_logger->getReports($filter_status, $filter_source);
    
    if ($format === 'csv') {
        header('Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8');
        header('Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="debug_reports_' . date('Y-m-d_His') . '.csv"');
        
        $output = fopen('php://output', 'w');
        fputcsv($output, ['ID', 'Date', 'Severity', 'Source', 'URL', 'User', 'Comment', 'Status']);
        
        foreach ($reports as $row) {
            fputcsv($output, [
                $row['id'],
                $row['date_added'],
                $row['severity'],
                $row['source'],
                $row['url'],
                $row['admin_user'] ?? '',
                $row['comment'],
                $row['status'] == 1 ? 'Closed' : 'Open'
            ]);
        }
        
        fclose($output);
        
    } elseif ($format === 'json') {
        header('Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8');
        header('Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="debug_reports_' . date('Y-m-d_His') . '.json"');
        
        echo json_encode($reports, JSON_PRETTY_PRINT | JSON_UNESCAPED_UNICODE);
    }
    
    exit;
}
```

