### ⭐ PRIORITÉ 2 - Features Avancées

#### 2.1 - Assignation d'utilisateurs
**Description:** Assigner un rapport à un utilisateur admin spécifique.

**SQL Migration:**
```sql
ALTER TABLE `oc_debug_logger_reports` 
ADD COLUMN `assigned_to` INT(11) NULL AFTER `admin_user`,
ADD KEY `idx_assigned` (`assigned_to`);
```

**UI (dans la page reports):**
```html
<!-- Dans chaque carte de rapport -->
<select class="form-select form-select-sm assign-user" data-report-id="<?= $rid ?>">
    <option value="">Unassigned</option>
    <?php foreach ($admin_users as $user): ?>
    <option value="<?= $user['user_id'] ?>" <?= $row['assigned_to'] == $user['user_id'] ? 'selected' : '' ?>>
        <?= htmlspecialchars($user['firstname'] . ' ' . $user['lastname']) ?>
    </option>
    <?php endforeach; ?>
</select>
```

**AJAX handler:**
```javascript
$(document).on('change', '.assign-user', function() {
    var reportId = $(this).data('report-id');
    var userId = $(this).val();
    
    fetch(cfg.assignUrl, {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {'Content-Type': 'application/json'},
        body: JSON.stringify({
            report_id: reportId,
            user_id: userId
        })
    });
});
```

